{
  "texts": [
    "However, we should not think that abduction captures the whole process of generating knowledge: \"Abductions alone do not add to present state knowledge, the full cycle of abduction-deduction-induction does.",
    "Abduction concludes with a question and is an invitation to further inquiry.",
    "Its conclusion proposes, could X possibly be the case?",
    "Let us find out.\"",
    "Abduction alone cannot generate knowledge, but it is an important starting point."
  ]
}